# Reading Age Checker — Flowise

Flowise implementation of the [Reading Age Checker](../README.md) flow. Built as an agentflow on Flowise 3.x.

## Requirements

- Flowise >= 3.0.0
- OpenAI API key (GPT-4o recommended; GPT-4o-mini supported with reduced rewrite quality) - Can also be switched for any model you require.

## Setup

1. In Flowise, go to **Agentflows → Add New**
2. Click the settings icon and choose **Import**
3. Upload `workflow.json`
4. Open the **Reading Age Analyser** agent node and connect your OpenAI credential
5. Save and test

## Configuration

| Node | Setting | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Reading Age Analyser | Model | `gpt-4o` | Downgrade to `gpt-4o-mini` to reduce cost; rewrite quality will decrease |
| Reading Age Analyser | Temperature | `0.2` | Keep low (0.1–0.3) for consistent scoring |
| Reading Age Analyser | Max Tokens | `4096` | Increase to `8192` for very long documents |
| Start | `target_reading_age` | `9` | Edit in Flow State to change the default target reading age |
| Start | `output_format` | `report` | Edit in Flow State — set to `rewrite-only` to return only the plain-English rewrite |

## Usage

Send a POST request to your Flowise agentflow endpoint:

```bash
curl -X POST \
  https://your-flowise-instance/api/v1/prediction/<agentflow-id> \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "question": "The Council hereby gives notice pursuant to Section 184 of the Highways Act 1980..."
  }'
```

To override the target reading age for a specific request, include it in your message:

```bash
curl -X POST \
  https://your-flowise-instance/api/v1/prediction/<agentflow-id> \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "question": "Please analyse this text for reading age 11: The Council hereby gives notice..."
  }'
```

## Response format

The flow returns a human-readable markdown report structured as follows:

```
## Reading age assessment

**Reading age: 21 — Very difficult**

This text is written at a reading age of 21, well above the GOV.UK recommended
level of 9. It contains very long sentences, passive voice, and legal jargon that
most readers will find difficult to understand.

---

## Issues found

- **Long sentence** "The Council of the London Borough of Southwark hereby gives notice..." — split into shorter sentences, leading with the key action
- **Passive voice** "must be received by the Head of Highways and Infrastructure" — change to "send your objection to the Head of Highways and Infrastructure"
- **Complex word** "facilitating" — use "helping" instead
- **Jargon** "pursuant to Section 184 of the Highways Act 1980" — explain as "under Section 184 of the Highways Act 1980"

---

## Plain-English rewrite

The Council of the London Borough of Southwark is giving notice under Section 184
of the Highways Act 1980. They plan to make a Temporary Traffic Regulation Order.
This will stop vehicles from using or waiting on the roads listed in the Schedule.
This is to help with construction and road works. If you want to object, write to
the Head of Highways and Infrastructure. They must receive your objection within
21 days of this Notice being published.

---

## Scores

| Measure                      | Score          |
|------------------------------|----------------|
| Flesch-Kincaid Reading Age   | 21.1           |
| Flesch Reading Ease          | 14.3 — Very difficult |
| Word count                   | 97             |
| Sentences                    | 2              |
| Average words per sentence   | 48.5           |
| Average syllables per word   | 1.9            |
```

## Extending this flow

- **Custom default reading age**: Change the `target_reading_age` value in the Start node's Flow State
- **Document upload**: Add a document loader node upstream of the agent to support PDF or DOCX file uploads
- **Batch processing**: Chain a second agent node to process documents section by section for inputs over 3,000 words
- **Custom jargon list**: Extend the system prompt with a department-specific list of terms to always flag

## Cost estimate

| Model | Typical input (500 words) | Typical output | Estimated cost per run |
|---|---|---|---|
| gpt-4o | ~750 tokens | ~1,500 tokens | ~$0.014 |
| gpt-4o-mini | ~750 tokens | ~1,500 tokens | ~$0.001 |

Costs correct as of April 2026. Check [OpenAI pricing](https://openai.com/pricing) for current rates.

## Known limitations

- Flesch-Kincaid scoring is approximated by the LLM, not computed algorithmically. For auditable exact scores, consider pre-processing with a library such as `textstat` (Python) before passing text to the flow
- Inputs over ~3,000 words may produce truncated output — split long documents into sections and run separately
- The plain-English rewrite must be reviewed by a human before publication, particularly for legal, clinical, or regulatory documents
- Non-English text is not supported in this version
- This is AI technology, always ensure you have got the correct clearance before using
